1
00:00:05,105 --> 00:00:09,195
Guru Maharaj told the
concept

2
00:00:09,195 --> 00:00:12,054
"Autocrat, Despot and Liar."

3
00:00:12,204 --> 00:00:15,603
[Autocrat, Despot and Liar]

4
00:00:16,003 --> 00:00:18,823
The devotees were shoсked
to hear those things,

5
00:00:18,930 --> 00:00:20,713
Autocrat, Despot, Liar...

6
00:00:20,713 --> 00:00:24,359
It just didn't sound 
like the normal way

7
00:00:24,359 --> 00:00:27,649
you describe God.

8
00:00:27,649 --> 00:00:31,229
[laughs]

9
00:00:33,209 --> 00:00:35,590
Or praise the Lord.

10
00:00:36,729 --> 00:00:40,273
Autocrat? Yes. Then 
in Hegelian terms—

11
00:00:40,273 --> 00:00:43,638
Reality is for Itself and by Itself.

12
00:00:44,450 --> 00:00:46,430
In the śloka before,

13
00:00:46,430 --> 00:00:49,340
abhijñaḥ svarāṭ 
[SB: 1.1.1]

14
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:53,517
He's for Himself and by Himself.

15
00:00:55,402 --> 00:00:57,267
As when Oscar Wilde told

16
00:00:57,267 --> 00:01:00,293
in the intro of the 
"Picture of Dorian Gray",

17
00:01:00,293 --> 00:01:03,340
"All art is quite useless."

18
00:01:03,687 --> 00:01:06,063
And what he meant to say

19
00:01:06,233 --> 00:01:08,771
in the "art is for art's sake" 
movement,

20
00:01:08,806 --> 00:01:13,233
"If it's really art, 
the highest type of art,

21
00:01:13,233 --> 00:01:17,516
then it doesn't exist to fulfill

22
00:01:17,516 --> 00:01:19,850
any secondary purpose.

23
00:01:19,850 --> 00:01:22,490
It exists for itself and by itself."

24
00:01:22,490 --> 00:01:23,953
That was he was saying.

25
00:01:23,953 --> 00:01:26,434
Of course he is applying it

26
00:01:26,434 --> 00:01:29,844
to mundane art.

27
00:01:29,988 --> 00:01:33,918
Even then he could 
understand this principle.

28
00:01:34,487 --> 00:01:36,797
That if it's gonna 
be glorified as art

29
00:01:36,806 --> 00:01:38,965
in the true sense,

30
00:01:38,965 --> 00:01:41,520
it must exist by itself
and for Itself,

31
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:43,400
for its own purpose.

32
00:01:43,406 --> 00:01:45,403
Not any secondary purpose.

33
00:01:45,403 --> 00:01:47,566
It's not useful—

34
00:01:47,566 --> 00:01:50,826
that's what he meant 
by saying "useless".

35
00:01:51,673 --> 00:01:54,387
You can't... Not only it's not useful

36
00:01:54,387 --> 00:01:55,760
for something else,

37
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:58,120
if you try to use it

38
00:01:58,132 --> 00:02:00,582
for another purpose,

39
00:02:01,151 --> 00:02:05,558
it turns into something else.

40
00:02:05,558 --> 00:02:07,949
And that's what he 
[Guru Mahārāj] is saying,

41
00:02:07,949 --> 00:02:10,778
"If you use Kṛṣṇa conception

42
00:02:10,778 --> 00:02:13,378
for some other purpose,

43
00:02:13,738 --> 00:02:16,888
then it's not Kṛṣṇa proper.

44
00:02:17,126 --> 00:02:20,335
It's in the name of Kṛṣṇa

45
00:02:20,335 --> 00:02:22,444
and looking like Kṛṣṇa,

46
00:02:22,444 --> 00:02:27,054
but it's not Kṛṣṇa proper."

47
00:02:28,150 --> 00:02:30,415
bhajanīya sarva-sad-guṇa viśiṣṭa

48
00:02:30,415 --> 00:02:31,353
Jīva Goswami is saying,

49
00:02:31,353 --> 00:02:33,698
"When you come in connection
with Kṛṣṇa proper,

50
00:02:33,698 --> 00:02:38,358
you won't try to use Him 
for your lower purpose,

51
00:02:38,362 --> 00:02:42,802
you will offer youself to Him,
for His higher purpose".

52
00:02:44,045 --> 00:02:46,875
That's Kṛṣṇa-conception,

53
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:50,485
that's why there has to be
the concept of the servitor

54
00:02:50,485 --> 00:02:52,939
and the servant and service,

55
00:02:52,939 --> 00:02:54,694
otherwise

56
00:02:57,096 --> 00:03:00,000
one may say, "Oh, 
I like Kṛṣṇa, I like God,

57
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,616
I like this, I like that".

58
00:03:01,616 --> 00:03:06,336
As long as He is fulfilling 
your lower purpose.

59
00:03:12,722 --> 00:03:16,792
Whereas we...

60
00:03:17,078 --> 00:03:19,323
I heard Guru Maharaj 
said today,

61
00:03:19,323 --> 00:03:22,602
"We are meant 
to be exploited by Him."

62
00:03:22,789 --> 00:03:25,946
He is not afraid 
to use that language.

63
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:32,266
However politically 
incorrect it might sound.

64
00:03:32,882 --> 00:03:36,579
We are trying to understand
the substance of the thing.

65
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:41,131
To be exploited by 
the Absolute Good

66
00:03:42,474 --> 00:03:43,756
is a good thing.

67
00:03:44,617 --> 00:03:49,253
Autocrat—He exists 
by Himself and for Himself

68
00:03:49,253 --> 00:03:51,782
to fulfill His own purpose.

69
00:03:51,939 --> 00:03:54,233
We are afraid, 
we are suspicious,

70
00:03:54,402 --> 00:03:59,028
but what do you think 
the purpose of the Absolute Good is?

71
00:04:00,312 --> 00:04:02,748
Then we need 
to understand the saḥ.

72
00:04:02,748 --> 00:04:04,988
Who is He? What is He?

73
00:04:05,325 --> 00:04:07,030
Rasa-rāj—

74
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:16,295
He is ecstasy personified.

75
00:04:19,015 --> 00:04:26,614
jyotir-abhyantare rūpaṁ
atulaṁ śyāmasundaram
[Nārada-pañcarātra]

76
00:04:26,614 --> 00:04:29,127
Beyond the light 
is the beautiful form

77
00:04:29,127 --> 00:04:31,338
of Śyāmasundar Kṛṣṇa.

78
00:04:31,823 --> 00:04:34,998
He is ecstasy personified,
beauty personified,

79
00:04:34,998 --> 00:04:40,206
sweetness personified,
love and affection personified.

80
00:04:45,194 --> 00:04:47,584
Autocrat. [Then,] Despot.

81
00:04:49,066 --> 00:04:51,468
Autocrat, Despot and Liar.

82
00:04:52,411 --> 00:04:54,432
He said, "Alright, Autocrat,

83
00:04:54,432 --> 00:04:55,728
we can understand something,

84
00:04:55,728 --> 00:04:58,476
but Despot?"
"Yes", he said, "Because

85
00:04:58,476 --> 00:05:01,922
if there is any check 
on His autocracy,

86
00:05:01,922 --> 00:05:04,604
we'll become the losers."

87
00:05:05,374 --> 00:05:07,006
Therefore Despot.

88
00:05:07,047 --> 00:05:10,208
He's the Absolute Good.

89
00:05:11,764 --> 00:05:19,609
It's not multi-cultural 
pluralistic ascending democracy,

90
00:05:19,609 --> 00:05:25,351
but descending 
autocratic despotic theocracy.

91
00:05:25,361 --> 00:05:28,199
Now people are really 
gonna be worried.

92
00:05:28,199 --> 00:05:31,327
[laughs]

93
00:05:33,497 --> 00:05:35,266
Of course He is the Absolute Good,

94
00:05:35,266 --> 00:05:38,535
do you want to check 
His movement?

95
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:44,322
The way you have 
to check in this world,

96
00:05:44,322 --> 00:05:47,642
look over your shoulder, 
cover your back.

97
00:05:48,177 --> 00:05:49,977
jīvo jīvasya jīvanam
[SB: 1.13.47]

98
00:05:49,977 --> 00:05:52,262
Because at every moment 
one living being

99
00:05:52,262 --> 00:05:54,752
is trying to exploit another.

100
00:05:54,887 --> 00:05:58,657
We don't want to be exploited.

101
00:06:04,764 --> 00:06:08,934
nimitta-mātraṁ bhava savya-sācin 
[BG: 11.33]

102
00:06:08,972 --> 00:06:11,242
Kṛṣṇa tells Arjuna,

103
00:06:11,242 --> 00:06:16,142
"It's already done, but

104
00:06:17,366 --> 00:06:21,366
as an instrument of Divine will

105
00:06:22,439 --> 00:06:25,199
you can offer yourself".

106
00:06:25,771 --> 00:06:29,857
And you will also get the credit.

107
00:06:29,857 --> 00:06:32,007
Autocrat, Despot

108
00:06:32,007 --> 00:06:39,541
Despot, so that His Absolute Good 
Autocracy is not checked.

109
00:06:39,541 --> 00:06:41,815
But Liar?

110
00:06:42,981 --> 00:06:45,378
When Guru Maharaj was explaining
this, a devotee said,

111
00:06:45,378 --> 00:06:46,985
"Ok, Autocrat, understood,

112
00:06:46,985 --> 00:06:50,864
Despot, understood.
But Liar?"

113
00:06:50,874 --> 00:06:57,211
He said, "Yes! Because
you are not ready to hear the truth!"

114
00:06:58,281 --> 00:07:01,808
So He has taken 
the position of a Liar.

115
00:07:02,728 --> 00:07:07,445
parokṣa-vādo vedo 'yaṁ
bālānām anuśāsanam 
[SB: 11.3.44]

116
00:07:07,798 --> 00:07:12,161
To gradually give you 
exposure to the truth.

117
00:07:12,161 --> 00:07:18,950
Like the way you teach a child.

118
00:07:21,634 --> 00:07:25,859
When Kṛṣṇa... 
when Yaśodā inquires from Kṛṣṇa

119
00:07:25,992 --> 00:07:30,171
at the behest of the cowherd boys 
complaining against Kṛṣṇa,

120
00:07:30,171 --> 00:07:34,439
"Have You eaten earth?" 
"No, they are just complaining

121
00:07:34,439 --> 00:07:36,628
because I'm beating 
them in play,

122
00:07:36,628 --> 00:07:39,658
and they are trying to get Me 
in trouble with you.

123
00:07:40,027 --> 00:07:43,703
You can see in My mouth
whether there is any earth or not."

124
00:07:44,283 --> 00:07:48,323
And Yaśodā sees within 
the mouth of Kṛṣṇa

125
00:07:48,345 --> 00:07:51,754
the Earth planet,

126
00:07:52,404 --> 00:07:55,646
all the solar system, 
the Milky way, the Universe,

127
00:07:55,646 --> 00:07:58,527
innumerable Universes...

128
00:08:01,290 --> 00:08:04,599
His lying is liberating

129
00:08:06,799 --> 00:08:09,435
because He is the Absolute Good.

